President Obama announced his intent to nominate Anne S. Ferro as Administrator of the Federal Motor Carrier Safety Administration, Ernie DuBester as a Member of the Federal Labor Relations Authority, and Julia A. Clark as General Counsel of the Federal Labor Relations Authority. Ferro has experience in highway safety and agency leadership, DuBester has 35 years of experience in labor-management relations, and Clark has practiced labor and employment law on behalf of unions and workers. President Obama expressed gratitude for their commitment to working families and helping America prosper.